The paper deals with the problem of counting triangles in graph streams, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms and data structures. The paper presents improved results on this problem, which suggests that it is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) to analyze the space complexity of the algorithms. Finally, the problem of counting triangles in graph streams is relevant to the area of streaming algorithms (cs.SI), which deals with algorithms that process data in a single pass or a small number of passes.
